HOUSE BILL 505
F1 6lr1577
By: Delegates Smith, Acevero, Davis, J. Long, and Toles
Introduced and read first time: January 27, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: February 28, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public and Nonpublic Schools – Student School Transfers – Academic Records
3 Documentation
4 FOR the purpose of requiring a public or nonpublic elementary or secondary school
5 receiving transfer of a student to accept certain unofficial documents to satisfy the
6 academic records requirement from the sending school under certain circumstances;
7 and generally relating to academic records documentation of students transferring
8 schools.
9 BY adding to
10 Article – Education
11 Section 7–118
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2025 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Education
17 7–118.
18 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “SCHOOL” MEANS A PUBLIC OR NONPUBLIC
19 ELEMENTARY OR SECONDARY SCHOOL.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0505*

2 HOUSE BILL 505
1 (B) FOR THE PURPOSE OF A STUDENT TRANSFERRING SCHOOLS, IF A
2 RECEIVING SCHOOL’S REQUEST FOR THE OFFICIAL ACADEMIC TRANSCRIPT AND
3 RECORDS OF THE TRANSFERRING STUDENT ARE DENIED BY THE SENDING SCHOOL
4 DUE TO A DISPUTE BETWEEN THE SENDING SCHOOL AND THE STUDENT, THE
5 RECEIVING SCHOOL SHALL ACCEPT THE FOLLOWING DOCUMENTATION FOR THE
6 SOLE PURPOSE OF ALLOWING THE STUDENT TO CONTINUE THE STUDENT’S
7 EDUCATION PROGRAM AT THE RECEIVING SCHOOL:
8 (1) AN UNOFFICIAL TRANSCRIPT;
9 (2) REPORT CARDS PROVIDED BY THE STUDENT;
10 (3) STANDARDIZED SUBJECT–RELEVANT STANDARDIZED TEST
11 SCORE REPORTS PROVIDED BY THE STUDENT; OR
12 (4) COPIES OF AWARDS AND HONORS DOCUMENTS;
13 (5) UNOFFICIAL ADVANCED PLACEMENT SCORE REPORTS OR
14 INTERNATIONAL BACCALAUREATE DIPLOMA PROGRAMME EXAMINATION
15 RESULTS; OR
16 (6) ANY OTHER UNOFFICIAL RECORD OR COPY OF A DOCUMENT
17 REGARDING THE TRANSFERRING STUDENT’S ACADEMIC RECORD THAT PROVIDES
18 EVIDENCE OF THE STUDENT’S COURSE OF STUDY AND RECORD OF PROGRESS AT THE
19 SENDING SCHOOL.
20 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
21 1, 2026.
Approved:
